Requirements:
	- Linux/UNIX environment
	- Apache web server with PHP5 installed
	- Perl 5, Perl modules: HTML::TreeBuilder (HTML-Tree-3.23),
	  Digest::SHA1, XML::LibXML; install modules using package manager,
	  cpan or downloaded tar archive. Please adjust PERL5LIB in
	  bin/prepare.sh in case HTML::TreeBuilder module is not installed
	  system-wide.
	- HTML tidy, iconv
	- Mozilla Firefox 2+ for annotation (other web browsers may not fully
	  work)

Installation:
- untar archive
- run ./install.sh to create a config file and build pavuk web downloader
  (patched to correctly download all css files)
- set web server access for victoria/www directory (other directories should
  not be accessible using the web server for security reasons)
- edit config, users and groups/* files
- run bin/import.pl to download pages in groups
- use Firefox to begin annotation

Note: this is a first & quick-and-dirty release of the Victoria annotation tool
